UID:5555-1777122000-1777132800@bloomspinweave.org
SUMMARY:Spin Silk\, Flax and Cotton
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, April 25\, 2026\, 1:00 – 4:00 PM. \n  \nParticipants will be introduced to three non-wool fibers that can be tricky to work with at first.  These three have wonderful properties and can\, with a little instruction and practice\, become important parts of your fiber and textile creations. Whether you desire drape\, luster\, absorption\, softness\, or thermal properties\, silk\, cotton\, and flax/linen can offer you all you’re looking for and more! \n  \n$55 BSWG members \n$65 non-BSWG student members (includes one-year guild student membership) \n$85 non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \n$10 additional\, due to the instructor\, for material kit at time of class. \n  \nREGISTRATION CLOSED. \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/spin-silk-flax-and-cotton
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bloomspinweave.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/25-Spinning-Silk-Flax.-Cotton-photo-DeVault.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Guild":MAILTO:educationbswg@gmail.com, newsletterbswg@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
